[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged over Hythe Hill stabbing of man, 70

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with the attempted murder of a pensioner, who was stabbed in his back garden.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Stuart Pain, 40, of Sydney Street, Brightlingsea, Essex, has been remanded in custody.
John Sales, 70, was attacked in Hythe Hill, Colchester, at about 17:40 GMT on Tuesday.
Mr Pain, who is unemployed, is due to appear at Colchester Magistrates' Court on Monday, police said.
